# OurSay — repo-root environment template
#
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in. Each workspace loads the repo-root `.env`
# FIRST, then its own `.env` (local overrides). This root file is for variables shared
# across workspaces; workspace-specific config (immudb, Postgres, anchoring, etc.) lives
# in that workspace's own example so nothing pluggable/incomplete is pinned at the root:
#   - immudb-test/.env.example   (immudb + Postgres + spike anchoring vars)
#   - turnkey-test/.env.example  (Turnkey)
#
# NEVER commit real secrets. `.env` and `*.key.json` are gitignored.
#
# Cross-workspace note (civic chain ids). `@oursay/api` POOLS every civic write under its own
# `CHAIN_ID` (default `ab-ca-gov`, the launch jurisdiction). The public-record settlement worker
# SETTLES + ANCHORS the set in `WORKER_CHAIN_IDS` (default `oursay-global,ab-ca-gov`: the universal
# record + the launch jurisdiction). The API's `CHAIN_ID` must be one of the worker's `WORKER_CHAIN_IDS`
# — the defaults already line up on `ab-ca-gov`, so `npm run dev -w @oursay/api` + `npm run worker -w
# public-record` settle the same pool with no extra config. Worker knobs live in
# `public-record/.env.example`. (Note: public-record's own `CHAIN_ID` library default is `oursay-global`,
# distinct from the API's `ab-ca-gov`.)

# --- Turnkey (historical spike; optional recovery only) ---
# Used by the turnkey-test spike. NOTE: Turnkey is NOT the identity backbone — that moved to
# passkeys + on-device HKDF + per-thread bindings (see turnkey-test/FINDINGS.md). Turnkey may
# remain only an optional account-recovery path.
TURNKEY_ORG_ID=
TURNKEY_API_PUB=
TURNKEY_API_PRIV=
# Optional: path (relative to repo root) to a Turnkey API key JSON with publicKey +
# privateKey fields. A `turnkey-api-credentials-*.key.json` at the repo root is
# auto-detected and overrides the values above.
# TURNKEY_API_KEY_FILE=./turnkey-api-credentials-XXXX.key.json
